    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architectural elements found mounted on the walls of roofed walkways in gardens. Stone slates are typically inscribed with the calligraphy or drawings of well-known figures. An inscription recording the construction of the garden also occasionally appears on the slates.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
